    <td valign="top"><p align="left">The American Literacy Council (ALC) provides resources and

    assistance to individuals and organizations involved in the literacy crisis in

      America and anywhere English is used. ALC provides software and other

      tools that help young and old alike improve

      their skill level in writing, reading and spelling.&nbsp;The chief

      offering is Sound-Write<font size="1"> (TM),</font> a Windows- based writing

      tool with instant audiovisual feedback and a

      50,000 word vocabulary.</p>

      <p align="left">To speak in person with an ALC representative please call

      (800)781-9985, email us at&nbsp; <a href="mailto:fyi@americanliteracy.com">fyi@americanliteracy.com</a>, or write

      to us at:&nbsp; American Literacy

    Council, 148 W. 117th Street, New York, NY&nbsp;10026.</p>

